---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Small Business Loan - Startup & Working Capital Funding | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <a href="#">Loans</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <span>Small Business Loan</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Small Business Loan</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Get affordable funding for your small business with loans from ₹1 lakh to ₹50 lakhs. Whether you need startup capital, working capital, or expansion funds, compare offers from 40+ lenders with rates starting at 11.50% p.a.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-indian-rupee-sign"></i>
          <span>Loan Amount: ₹1L - ₹50L</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-calendar-days"></i>
          <span>Tenure: 1-5 Years</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-percent"></i>
          <span>Interest: 11.50% onwards</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2>What is a Small Business Loan?</h2>
          <p>A small business loan is a financing solution designed for entrepreneurs, sole proprietors, partnerships, and small companies that need capital for day-to-day operations, inventory purchase, equipment acquisition, or business expansion. Unlike large corporate loans, small business loans feature simplified documentation, faster processing, and flexible repayment options tailored to the cash flow patterns of smaller enterprises.</p>
          <p>TrueCred Loan Expert connects small business owners with over 40 banks, NBFCs, and fintech lenders offering competitive small business loan products. Our platform evaluates your business based on multiple parameters including GST turnover, bank account transactions, and digital payments history — going beyond traditional financial statements. This approach helps businesses with strong performance but limited formal documentation access the credit they deserve.</p>

          <div class="info-grid">
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">11.50%</span>
              <span class="info-label">Interest Rate (p.a.)</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">₹50 Lakh</span>
              <span class="info-label">Max Loan Amount</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">5 Years</span>
              <span class="info-label">Max Tenure</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Small Business Loan Interest Rates — April 2026</h3>
          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Bank / NBFC</th>
                <th>Interest Rate (p.a.)</th>
                <th>Processing Fee</th>
                <th>Max Tenure</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>HDFC Bank</td>
                <td>12.00% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 2.00%</td>
                <td>4 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>ICICI Bank</td>
                <td>12.50% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 2.25%</td>
                <td>5 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Bajaj Finserv</td>
                <td>11.50% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 3.00%</td>
                <td>5 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Lendingkart</td>
                <td>14.00% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 2.50%</td>
                <td>3 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>NeoGrowth</td>
                <td>13.50% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 2.00%</td>
                <td>3 Years</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h3>Eligibility Criteria</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Business operational for at least 1 year with verifiable revenue</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Minimum annual turnover of ₹5,00,000 (₹3,00,000 for micro businesses)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Business owner aged between 23 and 60 years</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Personal CIBIL score of 680 or above</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Valid business registration — GST, Shop Act, or Udyam certificate</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Active business bank account with regular transactions for 6+ months</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>How to Get a Small Business Loan</h3>
          <div class="steps-grid">
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">1</div>
              <h4>Check Eligibility</h4>
              <p>Enter your business details — type, turnover, vintage, and loan requirement — to check eligibility across 40+ lenders instantly.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">2</div>
              <h4>Get Matched</h4>
              <p>Our algorithm matches you with lenders most likely to approve your profile based on your business metrics and credit history.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">3</div>
              <h4>Upload Documents</h4>
              <p>Submit GST returns, bank statements, and KYC documents digitally. No branch visits needed for most applications.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">4</div>
              <h4>Receive Funding</h4>
              <p>Get approval within 24-72 hours and funds disbursed to your business account. Repay in convenient monthly EMIs.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Documents Required</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Business registration — GST certificate, Shop Act license, partnership deed, or Udyam certificate</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Last 12 months GST returns (GSTR-3B) or sales invoices</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Last 6-12 months bank statements of the business account</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> KYC documents of business owner — Aadhaar, PAN, and address proof</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Business address proof — utility bill, rent agreement, or ownership document</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Latest ITR (if available) or certified financial statements</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-file-signature"></i> Apply for Small Business Loan</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Full Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input" required>
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Loan Amount</option>
                  <option value="100000">₹1,00,000</option>
                  <option value="200000">₹2,00,000</option>
                  <option value="500000">₹5,00,000</option>
                  <option value="1000000">₹10,00,000</option>
                  <option value="2000000">₹20,00,000</option>
                  <option value="3000000">₹30,00,000</option>
                  <option value="5000000">₹50,00,000</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="City" required>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">
                Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
              </button>
            </form>
          </div>

          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-link"></i> Quick Links</h3>
            <div class="sidebar-links">
              <a href="/pages/business-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Business Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/home-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Home Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/loan-against-property"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Loan Against Property</a>
              <a href="/pages/gold-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Gold Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/education-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Education Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/car-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Car Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Cards</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-score"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Score</a>
              <a href="/pages/calculators"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> EMI Calculator</a>
              <a href="/pages/insurance"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Insurance</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">Got Questions?</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p>Common questions about small business loans.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Can I get a business loan without collateral?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Yes, most small business loans up to ₹50 lakhs on TrueCred are unsecured and don't require any collateral. Lenders evaluate your business based on revenue, bank statements, GST turnover, and credit score. For CGTMSE-backed loans, the government provides a guarantee in lieu of collateral, covering loans up to ₹2 crore for eligible MSMEs.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            What types of businesses qualify for a small business loan?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              All types of legitimate businesses qualify, including retail shops, restaurants, manufacturing units, service businesses, e-commerce sellers, freelancers, professionals (doctors, CAs, lawyers), trading businesses, and contractors. The business must be registered and operational with verifiable revenue. Even home-based businesses and online sellers with GST registration can apply.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            How much loan can I get for my small business?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Loan amounts range from ₹1 lakh to ₹50 lakhs for unsecured small business loans. The amount depends on your annual turnover (typically 10-25% of turnover), business vintage, credit score, and existing liabilities. Businesses with strong financials and a good relationship with their bank may qualify for higher amounts up to ₹75 lakhs to ₹1 crore.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            What if my business doesn't have formal financial statements?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Many fintech lenders on TrueCred use alternative assessment methods for businesses without formal statements. They analyze GST returns, digital payment histories (UPI, POS transactions), bank account statements, and e-commerce sales data to assess creditworthiness. This is particularly helpful for small retailers, food businesses, and service providers who may not maintain audited books.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Can I use a small business loan for any purpose?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Most small business loans are general-purpose and can be used for working capital, inventory purchase, equipment buying, shop renovation, marketing, hiring, technology upgrades, or any legitimate business expense. However, lenders do not permit use for personal expenses, speculation, or non-business activities. Some scheme-specific loans (like equipment finance) may have end-use restrictions.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page CTA -->
  <section class="page-content" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-cta">
        <div>
          <h3>Fuel Your Business Growth with the Right Loan</h3>
          <p>Compare offers from 40+ lenders. Get up to ₹50 lakhs for your small business at competitive rates.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline" style="color:#fff;border:2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.5);padding:14px 32px;font-size:0.95rem;">
          Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
